data.name: lblTGC1.Text
data.value: 1. If you would like to delete a Template Group, select the desired Template Group in the drop down then click the [Delete Group] button. It will delete all associated Templates to that Template Group.

data.name: textBox7.Text
data.value: 1. For the desired Template, modify the value by typing or clicking in the order field. Remember, to commit any changes it is required to click [Save Changes] at the bottom of the template. To discard any changes, click [Discard Changes].

data.name: textBox9.Text
data.value: 1. Either by clicking on the header or body of the button, it will pop out a customization form. You may edit the text in the header, body, and select the colour of the button. Clicking [Save] will display the changes to the button in the template, but remember to commit the change you must click [Save Changes] on the template itself.

data.name: textBox15.Text
data.value: 1. For the desired template, clicking on [Transfer To Group] will pop out a form to prompt the user to select the destination group. Clicking on [Transfer] will transfer the group to the selected Template Group.

data.name: textBox17.Text
data.value: 1. Clicking on [Template Export] will export the project's SQL table data to a notepad text file and the location will be displayed in the section below. While not awfully useful, you can see the raw data.
